  "text": "In previous investigations [CITATION_1] , the above parameters have been successfully used to characterise the nature of a class, and understand the most appropriate allocation. Moreover, since they do not require substantial computations, they can be calculated at run time, just before an object is instantiated. In any case they need to be determined just once for each application class.",
